         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/3/88 ¶  ¶ Herewith, dear Mr Ridley, I beg to send you fragments of two Papuan orchids, taken from plants in the horticultural Establishment of Mr Benj. Gulliver of Townsville, after whom I should l...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.03.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Ridley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Archives, Miscellaneous correspondence.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/3/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith, dear Mr Ridley, I beg to send you fragments of two Papuan orchids, taken from plants in the horticultural Establishment of Mr Benj. Gulliver of Townsville, after whom I should like one to be named, the large-flowered Spec. of Dendrobium seemingly being new.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium</seg> species named after Gulliver has been found.</p>
               </note> But as I am trying to bring the difficult “Key”<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.05.03.</p>
               </note> to a speedy conclusion, I shall have no leisure to enter on a critical examination of these spec. Dendrobium so send them to you, who has gained the most recent experience on them. This will give you also an opportunity, to set right the nomenclature of <name key="Dendrobium%20Johnsoniae%20">Dendrobium Johnsoniae </name>and D. Macfarlanei, as described by myself.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to H. Ridley, 21 February 1887, and M to H. Ridley,17 May 1887.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will be able to give Mr Forbes a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">generic</hi>
               </seg> list of his plants; that is really all he wants for his volume of travels. He will have seen a <name key="Vitis%20">Vitis </name>named by Planchon after him, from a specimen forwarded by me to Montpellier<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No eponymous orchid species have been found in IPNI.</p>
               </note> - Radlkofer can furnish the names of his Sapindaceae; he had them all long ago. I will <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">soon</hi>
               </seg> do something to a portion of the Dicotyledones.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that Mr Britten<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Britten.</p>
               </note> will deal generously and unprejudiced by mere […]<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>and unprejudiced by mere […] <seg style="font-style: italic; ">interlined, one illegible word.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> with my Key in reviewing it; the explanatory essay will likely appear in May. <note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See B89.05.04. The paper was read before the Royal Society of NSW in October 1888. See Lucas, Maroske &amp; Brown-May (2006), pp. 46-50.</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>You know of course that <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg> other languages have the diminutive for flower heads. Ovulary is better than germen, ovary absolutely incorrect. Beak, wings, head, claws, palate, throat, vagina, abortion, spur, mouth, ear, chin, beard, lips &amp;c should be restricted to zoologic organography</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Best compl. to Mr Carruthers.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the left margin of the back of the folio.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please publish the Dendrobium if new, in Mr Brittens journal<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of botany</seg>. Written in the central margin of the back of the folio.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dendrobium%20Johnsoniae%20">Dendrobium Johnsoniae </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dendrobium%20Macfarlanei%20">Dendrobium Macfarlanei </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dicotyledoneae">Dicotyledoneae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sapindaceae%20">Sapindaceae </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Vitis%20">Vitis </name>
            </p>
         </div>
